==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: -gram
<hw>-gram</hw> <pr>(-gr⟦acr⟧m)</pr>. <ety>[Gr. <grk>gra`mma</grk> a
thing drawn or written, a letter, fr. <grk>gra`fein</grk> to draw,
write. See <er>Graphic.</er>]</ety> <def>A suffix indicating something
drawn or written, a drawing, writing; -- as, monogram, telegram,
chronogram.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gram</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Gram
<hw>Gram</hw> <pr>(gr⟦acr⟧m)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>gram</ets>; akin to E. <ets>grim</ets>. ⟦root⟧35.]</ety>
<def>Angry.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Havelok, the
Dane.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gram</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Gram
<hw>Gram</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pg. <ets>gr⟦atil⟧o</ets> grain. See
<er>Grain.</er>]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The East Indian name of
the chick-pea (<spn>Cicer arietinum</spn>) and its seeds; also, other
similar seeds there used for food.</def></p>

<p><ent>Gramme</ent>⟦br⟧
